# `az acr build` uploads this whole directory to Azure as the build context, so what
# is excluded here is a security control, not a size optimisation. This repo has a
# habit of dropping .env files around (see .gitignore), and one of them landing in an
# image layer would ship the Event Hubs key to the registry — where it would sit,
# readable, in every pull.
#
# The image needs exactly two files from this directory: red_point_detector.py and
# entrypoint.sh. Everything else is noise at best.
.env
.env.*
*.env
*.pem
*.key
*secret*
*credential*
id_rsa*
.git/

__pycache__/
*.pyc
